He received serious burns to both arms and superficial burns to his hands, police said.

His injuries are not considered life-threatening and he is undergoing treatment at the Flinders Medical Centre.

Police have charged a 16-year-old boy from Morphett Vale and a 19-year-old man from Reynella East with committing acts to cause harm.

